The paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze urban big data and identify causal pathways for air pollutants. This suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of Bayesian learning and graphical models could place it under databases (cs.DB) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the focus on air quality data and meteorological data could also suggest information retrieval (cs.IR) as a possible sub-category.
